# Makefile Quick Reference

## Basic Usage

```bash
# Build everything
make build

# Run tests
make test

# Clean build artifacts
make clean

# Build and test
make build test
```

## ROS Version Detection

The Makefile automatically detects ROS version from environment:
- ROS1: Uses `ROS_DISTRO` (noetic, melodic, etc.)
- ROS2: Uses `ROS_VERSION=2` or `ROS_DISTRO` (humble, jazzy, rolling)

## Examples

### ROS1 (Noetic)
```bash
source /opt/ros/noetic/setup.bash
make build
make test
```

### ROS2 (Humble)
```bash
source /opt/ros/humble/setup.bash
make build
make test
```

### Debug Build
```bash
make debug
```

### Release Build
```bash
make release
```

### Docker Build
```bash
make docker-build-ros1
make docker-build-ros2-humble
```

## Advanced Targets

- `make rust-build` - Build only Rust library
- `make rust-test` - Test only Rust code
- `make cpp-build` - Build only C++ code
- `make cpp-test` - Test only C++ code
- `make format` - Format code (requires formatters)
- `make lint` - Lint code (requires linters)
- `make install` - Install package











